President Barack Obama issued a statement on Portugal Day, also known as the Day of Camões, Portugal, and the Portuguese Communities. He expressed his best wishes to those who celebrate this day and highlighted the strong friendship between the United States and Portugal. The two nations work together to promote peace, stability, and development worldwide. The day also commemorates the passing of Portugal's greatest poet, Luís Vaz de Camões, and celebrates the country's history and achievements. The President acknowledged the significant contributions of Portuguese-Americans to the United States, enriching the nation with their culture and heritage.